mplate","17":"/home/runner/work/nixcafe-docs/nixcafe-docs/apps/develop-templates/src/pages/index.mdx#develop-templates","18":"/home/runner/work/nixcafe-docs/nixcafe-docs/apps/develop-templates/src/pages/index.mdx#why-nix-flake-templates"},"fieldIds":{"category":0,"subtitle":1,"text":2,"title":3,"titles":4},"fieldLength":{"0":[0,0,19,1,0],"1":[0,0,28,2,1],"2":[0,0,7,4,1],"3":[0,0,85,5,1],"4":[0,0,13,3,6],"5":[0,0,30,4,6],"6":[0,0,37,2,1],"7":[0,0,73,2,0],"8":[0,0,5,2,3],"9":[0,0,5,1,3],"10":[0,0,5,1,3],"11":[0,0,5,1,3],"12":[0,0,10,2,0],"13":[0,0,10,4,2],"14":[0,0,18,3,2],"15":[0,0,20,3,2],"16":[0,0,25,2,2],"17":[0,0,69,2,0],"18":[0,0,67,4,2]},"averageFieldLength":[0,0,27.94736842105263,2.526315789473684,2],"storedFields":{"0":{"category":"","href":"/contributing#contributing","subtitle":"","text":" This project follows GitHub Flow. All contributions must be made via pull requests against the main branch.","title":"Contributing","titles":[],"type":"page"},"1":{"category":"","href":"/contributing#development-shell","subtitle":"","text":" git clone https://github.com/nixcafe/develop-templates.git\ncd develop-templates\nnix develop The dev shell provides nixfmt, deadnix, and statix with git-hooks enabled. Formatting and linting run automatically on every commit.","title":"Development Shell","titles":["Contributing"],"type":"section"},"2":{"category":"","href":"/contributing#creating-a-feature-branch","subtitle":"","text":" git checkout -b feat/my-new-template","title":"Creating a Feature Branch","titles":["Contributing"],"type":"section"},"3":{"category":"","href":"/contributing#adding-a-new-nix-template","subtitle":"","text":" Create a repository under nixcafe-develop with your template files (a standard flake.nix + flake.lock)Add the repository as a flake input in flake.nix: templates-<name> = {\n  url = \"github:nixcafe-develop/<repo-name>\";\n  flake = false;\n}; Create templates/<name>/default.nix: { inputs, ... }:\n{\n  description = \"Description of your template\";\n  path = \"${inputs.templates-<name>}\";\n  welcomeText = ''\n    # Template Name — Nix Development Environment\n    Run `nix develop` to enter the dev shell.\n  '';\n} Run git-hooks checks manually if needed: nix flake check Open a pull request to the main branch. All PRs require at least one approving review and must pass CI checks before merging.","title":"Adding a New Nix Template","titles":["Contributing"],"type":"section"},"4":{"category":"","href":"/contributing#on-pull-request","subtitle":"","text":" Git hooks checks (nixfmt, deadnix, statix) run automatically on all PRs.","title":"On Pull Request","titles":["Contributing","CI/CD (GitHub Actions)"],"type":"section"},"5":{"category":"","href":"/contributing#on-push-to-main","subtitle":"","text":" The Nix flake is automatically published to FlakeHub as nixcafe/develop-templates with rolling versioning. This ensures flakes consuming these templates are not affected by GitHub API rate limits.","title":"On Push to Main","titles":["Contributing","CI/CD (GitHub Actions)"],"type":"section"},"6":{"category":"","href":"/contributing#branch-protection","subtitle":"","text":" The main branch is protected: Pull request reviews are required (at least 1 approval)Status checks must pass before mergingStale reviews are dismissed when new commits are pushed All development happens on feature branches and is merged to main via pull requests.","title":"Branch Protection","titles":["Contributing"],"type":"section"},"7":{"category":"","href":"/templates#available-templates","subtitle":"","text":" TemplateLanguage / Use CaseDescriptioncolmena-configNixOS DeploymentNixOS Configuration with Colmena deploymentjavaJava / JVMJava development environment with JDK, Maven, and GradlekotlinKotlin / JVMKotlin development environment with Kotlin compiler and GradlenixNixNix development environment with nixfmt, deadnix, statix (default)nix-configNixOSNixOS system configuration flake templatenodeNode.js / JavaScript / TypeScriptNode.js development environment with npm, yarn, pnpm, and corepackpythonPythonPython development environment with pip, venv, and uvrustRustRust development environment with cargo, rustc, rustfmt, clippy, and rust-analyzersecretsSecrets ManagementEncrypted secrets management with agenix or sops-nix integration","title":"Available Templates","titles":[],"type":"page"},"8":{"category":"","href":"/templates#nodejs","subtitle":"","text":" nix flake init -t beans#node","title":"Node.js","titles":["Available Templates","Usage Examples"],"type":"section"},"9":{"category":"","href":"/templates#python","subtitle":"","text":" nix flake init -t beans#python","title":"Python","titles":["Available Templates","Usage Examples"],"type":"section"},"10":{"category":"","href":"/templates#rust","subtitle":"","text":" nix flake init -t beans#rust","title":"Rust","titles":["Available Templates","Usage Examples"],"type":"section"},"11":{"category":"","href":"/templates#java","subtitle":"","text":" nix flake init -t beans#java","title":"Java","titles":["Available Templates","Usage Examples"],"type":"section"},"12":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#quick-start","subtitle":"","text":" nix flake init -t \"github:nixcafe/develop-templates#${template_name}\" --refresh","title":"Quick Start","titles":[],"type":"page"},"13":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#nix-flake-init-direct","subtitle":"","text":" nix flake init -t \"github:nixcafe/develop-templates#${template_name}\" --refresh","title":"nix flake init (direct)","titles":["Quick Start"],"type":"section"},"14":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#nix-registry-recommended","subtitle":"","text":" Add to your Nix registry for shorter commands: nix registry add beans \"github:nixcafe/develop-templates\"\nnix flake init -t beans#${template_name}","title":"nix registry (recommended)","titles":["Quick Start"],"type":"section"},"15":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#with-cattery-modules","subtitle":"","text":" If you use cattery-modules for NixOS deployment, the templates are pre-registered: nix flake init -t beans#${template_name}","title":"With Cattery Modules","titles":["Quick Start"],"type":"section"},"16":{"category":"","href":"/quick-start#default-template","subtitle":"","text":" The default template is nix — a Nix development shell with formatting, linting, and dead code detection tools. Used when no template is specified. nix flake init -t beans","title":"Default Template","titles":["Quick Start"],"type":"section"},"17":{"category":"","href":"/#develop-templates","subtitle":"","text":" Nix flake templates for reproducible development environments — bootstrap Node.js, Python, Rust, Java, Kotlin, NixOS configs, and more with a single command. A curated collection of Nix flake project templates. Bootstrap reproducible development environments for any programming language with nix flake init -t. Drop-in replacements for language-specific version managers — powered by Nix, no Docker, no manual toolchain setup. Each template is a thin wrapper that pulls its content from a dedicated repository under nixcafe-develop. Templates are managed as Nix flake inputs (no git submodules).","title":"develop-templates","titles":[],"type":"page"},"18":{"category":"","href":"/#why-nix-flake-templates","subtitle":"","text":" Reproducible — identical development environments across Linux, macOS, and WSLNo Docker overhead — native builds with Nix, no container runtime neededDeclarative — define your dev tools, dependencies, and environment variables in one flake.nixZero-install bootstrap — nix flake init -t + nix develop and you're ready to codePolyglot — one toolchain to manage dev environments for all programming languagesCI-friendly — same environment locally and in GitHub Actions / GitLab CI","title":"Why Nix Flake Templates?","titles":["develop-templates"],"type":"section"}},"dirtCount":0,"index":[["zero",{"2":{"18":1}}],["quick",{"3":{"12":1},"4":{"13":1,"14":1,"15":1,"16":1}}],["you're",{"2":{"18":1}}],["you",{"2":{"15":1}}],[